          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^{p,q}]]></fr:tex> is a bigraded object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {A}]]></fr:tex> such that

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^{p,q}=0]]></fr:tex> except for a finite number of pairs <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(p,q)]]></fr:tex>, and
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^{p,q}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+q\neq  n]]></fr:tex>
      </html:li>

    </html:ol>


    
    then we define two <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-opposite filtrations of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\sum _{p,q}A^{p,q}]]></fr:tex> by setting

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>740</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1.2.4.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         F^p(A)         = \sum _{p'\geqslant  p} A^{p',q'}       \tag{1.2.4.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>741</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1.2.4.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \overline {F}^q(A)         = \sum _{q'\geqslant  q} A^{p',q'}.       \tag{1.2.4.2}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    We have

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>742</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-1.2.4.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1.2.4.3</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {Gr}_F^p\operatorname {Gr}_{\overline {F}}^q(A)         = A^{p,q}.       \tag{1.2.4.3}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
